.TH "psc_i2s_set_fmt" 9 "psc_i2s_set_fmt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
psc_i2s_set_fmt \- set the serial format.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" psc_i2s_set_fmt
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dai *cpu_dai "  ","
.BI "unsigned int format "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu_dai" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "format" 12
one of SND_SOC_DAIFMT_xxx
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This function is called by the machine driver to tell us what serial
format to use.

This driver only supports I2S mode.  Return an error if the format is
not SND_SOC_DAIFMT_I2S.
